what happens in another year?  unless they stop upgrading, warriors will have near 10k hps.  something must be done, now.  my fav idea is giving druids a 33% heal, maybe done over time, i dont care.  or give us some uniqueness in Damage dealing on raids, either direct or by increaseing damage dealt by others. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhuzurdadi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Huzurdadi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/8/02 1:23:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27012.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why beat around the bush?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
You've missed the entire point of our petition.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think that your entire petition is a waste of time since it asks for a number of items which really don't address the core issue. And the reason why you don't address the core issue is because you are afraid of the b*tching that clerics will do when you do address the central issue.<br>
<br>
Simply explain, as if it needs explaining, that CH is tremendously more powerful than any other heal in the game. Since it is the only spell that scales in power as tanks (and heck any other character) scales in power it is by definition unbalanced wrt. other constant heals. <br>
<br>
For other healers to maintain a constant ratio of effectiveness with clerics they need a heal which scales. <br>
<br>
Thus, I recommended giving the other healers a scaling heal that is 66% as mana effective as cleric healing. What ratio do you think clerics want? The current x4 ratio? Sounds a little messed up, doesn't it?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=leadar>Leadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/8/02 1:31:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27012.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why beat around the bush?</span><hr size=1> Yep yep.  I &quot;heard&quot; that they will be increasing the power of the players (yet again) when the &quot;Planes of Power&quot; is released.  Some people were talking about levels to 70?  Not that this has been confirmed anywhere, that I have seen.  <br>
<br>
If this is going to happen, then druids/shaman abilities to heal are going to be even more minuscule than they are now.  The more they upgrade tanks, the less need there is for a druid to<br>
heal.  If they allow chars to get to level 70, (or some equivalent in skills/abilities) then our ability to heal is going to be laughable.<br>
<br>
Many people complain about druids/shaman getting CH, and their argument(s) against it usually are:<br>
<br>
1. “if druids/shaman get CH, it will trivialize encounters, and the VI staff will upgrade mobs to ungodly levels to compensate”.  <br>
<br>
My retort to this is, havent they already done so?  Don’t they (or havent they), when they create(d) new Velious/Luclin mobs, take they CH rotations into consideration.  Don’t they<br>
assume that the top guilds on each server will have a multitude of lvl 60 clerics at their disposal when attempting these boss mobs?  Therefor, they ALREADY have buffed up the mobs with the consideration that there will be a bunch (more than an adequate number) of CH’s there at the<br>
raids disposal.  So what does it matter if the Complete Healers are clerics, or if they are druids, or if they are shaman?  For this particular argument it doesnt matter (imo).  <br>
<br>
2.  “if druids/shaman get CH, who would want to play a cleric?” <br>
<br>
Clerics still get the ultimate rez.  They still have CH.  They still have the best buffs.  They (VI) could make it so that shaman/druids get CH at a much larger mana cost, and/or slower cast time.  They could give clerics some additional spells (spells that would give clerics the ability to solo<br>
for exp, or solo easier, if they need).  Oh, but you say, clerics don’t want to solo at the high end of the game?  (Well, now you are thinking like druids.  We really don’t want to solo at the high end of the game either.  But, I digress.)  Clerics buffs would still be stronger, their healing abilities would be more mana efficient and faster, and they would still be the most desireable healer for a group.  <br>
<br>
Summary: <br>
<br>
I know VI wont ever give druids/shaman the same CH as they give clerics.  But, some variation is needed.  A much stronger heal, or a % heal, or a CH that costs much more mana than a cleric’s and/or takes longer to cast, something.  <br>
<br>
Leadar<br>
<br>
