<br>
But yes, CH dominates healing in the high level game, and thus breaks healing for other priest classes.  A 2000 or 3000 point heal wouldn't enable shaman and druids to keep up in a high level raid, where the cleric team is sequentially casting CH every 3 to 5 seconds on the MT. <br>
<br>
So we (meaning druids) have to look elsewhere for healing contributions on the high level raid.  One such area is AoE healing, due to the AoE damage effects of many of these mobs.  Paladins are better healers on high level raids than druids for this reason. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=leadar>Leadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/8/02 3:09:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27012.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why beat around the bush?</span><hr size=1> Scirocco, <br>
<br>
Im sure they would love to have never introduced CH into the game.  But, VI could NEVER take CH out of the game now, unless they totally re-did all of the upper end mobs since the Velious/Luclin expansions.  Because all the upper end mobs were created in these expansions with CH in mind.  <br>
<br>
Therefore, the cat is out of the bag, and is not going back in the bag, without significant effort.  CH is obviously intended to be used in these encounters.  <br>
<br>
Do I think they will, or should, give other priests the same CH as they give clerics? No.  Should they do something else to help? Yes. <br>
